SIMPLE: plunk
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plunk
<hw>Plunk</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Imitative.]</ety>
<mark>[Chiefly Colloq.]</mark> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To pluck and release
quickly (a musical string); to twang.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To throw, push, drive heavily, plumply, or suddenly;
<as>as, to <ex>plunk</ex> down a dollar</as>; also, to hit or
strike.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To be a truant from (school).</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plunk</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Plunk
<hw>Plunk</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <mark>[Chiefly Colloq.]</mark>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To make a quick, hollow, metallic, or harsh sound, as
by pulling hard on a taut string and quickly releasing it; of a raven,
to croak.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To drop or sink down suddenly or heavily; to
plump.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To play truant, or ⟦ldquo⟧hooky⟦rdquo⟧.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plunk</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Plunk
<hw>Plunk</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Act or sound of
plunking.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <mark>[Slang]</mark> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A large sum of
money.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A dollar.</def>
<mark>[U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plunket</ent>⟦br⟧
